paragraphs.text:
%md

Let's assume that one customer logs in and the system needs to calculate the recommended product list.

Run this query on Graph Visualization to see the products purchased by the customer 12346.

```
SELECT *
MATCH (c1)-[e1]->(p1)
WHERE ID(c1) = 'cust_12346'
```

Two hops:

```
SELECT *
MATCH (c1)-[e1]->(p1)<-[e2]-(c2)
WHERE ID(c1) = 'cust_12346'
  AND ID(c1) != ID(c2)
```

Three hops:

```
SELECT *
MATCH (c1)-[e1]->(p1)<-[e2]-(c2)-[e3]->(p2)
WHERE ID(c1) = 'cust_12346'
  AND ID(c1) != ID(c2)
  AND ID(p1) != ID(p2)
```

%pgx
vertexSet = graph.createVertexSet()
rs = graph.queryPgql("SELECT c MATCH (c:Customer) WHERE ID(c) = 'cust_12346'")
for (r in rs) {
    vertex = r.getVertex(1)
    vertexSet.add(vertex)
    analyst.personalizedPagerank(graph, vertexSet)
}

%pgx
graph.queryPgql("""
  SELECT ID(p), p.pagerank, p.description
  MATCH (p)
  WHERE LABEL(p) = 'Product'
    AND NOT EXISTS (
      SELECT *
      MATCH (p)-[:purchased_by]->(c)
      WHERE ID(c) = 'cust_12346'
    )
  ORDER BY p.pagerank DESC
  LIMIT 10
""")

  WHERE ID(c) = 'cust_12346'
    AND ID(p) = 'prod_85123A'
""")
